cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is about image-to-image translation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new GAN model architecture and optimization strategy, which involves machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Thus, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the limitations of existing symmetric GAN models and proposes an asymmetric model, which involves graph theory (GR) concepts. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed model on several publicly available datasets, which involves multimedia (MM) research.
